    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received May 6.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 512.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In answer to your No. 409, of April 4,
                            regarding an apprehended massacre of Christians in Turkey, and the
                            proposed visit of the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> to Smyrna,
                            Alexandretta, and Beirut, I have to inform you that for the last three
                            weeks tranquility seems to exist in the provinces, and I see no cause to
                            fear present danger. The pledges given me for energetic official action,
                            I feel sure, have been complied with.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
